<item>
            <title>[HBASE-7196] &apos;hbase shell status&apos; throws exception when HBase is not running</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-7196</link>
                <project id="12310753" key="HBASE">HBase</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Its kind of a nuisance bug. One would assume that &apos;status&apos; command should simply  return something along the lines of &quot;HBase is not running&quot;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12616947">HBASE-7196</key>
            <summary>&apos;hbase shell status&apos; throws exception when HBase is not running</summary>
                <type id="1" iconUrl="https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/issuetypes/bug.png">Bug</type>
